text.text:
I rarely write reviews, but this experience was beyond unacceptable. From the moment I checked in, it was clear this hotel has no regard for cleanliness, service, or basic hospitality.

The room was filthy — stained sheets, a foul odor, and dust covering every surface. The bathroom looked like it hadn’t been cleaned in weeks; mold on the tiles, hair in the drain, and no hot water.

Staff were completely indifferent — rude at check-in and nowhere to be found when needed. I requested a room change, and they flatly refused, offering no explanation or apology.

Noise levels were unbearable all night, with people shouting in the halls and music blasting from nearby rooms. Despite repeated complaints, management did absolutely nothing.

The pictures online are completely misleading — what you see is not what you get. This place feels like a rundown lodge, not a functioning hotel.

I checked out a day early and didn’t get so much as a “sorry.” Do yourself a favor — spend your money anywhere else. This was the worst hotel experience I’ve ever had.

text.text: **Review: Disappointing Stay at Venture Park – Not Recommended for Families I stayed at Venture Park for 15 days with a group of friends, and unfortunately, our experience was quite disappointing. Here are the key issues we faced during our stay: **1. Poor Air Conditioning and Maintenance** The air conditioning in the room was in terrible condition. It lacked regular maintenance, was full of dust, and didn’t cool the room properly. The remote controls were confusing, with no visible labels or names. Additionally, the AC unit was constantly dripping water inside the room, making the floor wet and uncomfortable. **2. Inadequate Bathroom Privacy** The bathroom windows were oddly positioned and very low. At a height of 5'7", I felt exposed while using the bathroom as the glass window started around chest level. Although the glass appeared to be frosted, it still didn't offer a sense of proper privacy. This is a serious concern, especially for anyone staying with family. **3. Unprofessional Night Receptionist** The night shift staff was extremely rude and uncooperative. We worked day shifts and returned to the room around 8 PM, and whenever we raised issues, he responded with arrogance and dismissed our concerns. Despite reporting the same problems multiple times, there was no action or support provided. **4. No Refund Policy Made It Worse** We had already paid for the 15 days in full and were told the payment was non-refundable. This left us with no option but to stay, despite the ongoing problems. **Conclusion** Based on my experience, I would not recommend Venture Park, especially for families. It might be tolerable for a short one-night stay with friends, but even then, be prepared for discomfort and lack of service.

Although the rooms are spacious, the hotel needs improvements in terms of electrical and washroom fittings. Bathroom fittings are rusted, and the pipe is difficult to open and starts leaking. I have uploaded the images. My feedback has been shared with the hotel staff, and they assured me that these fittings will be replaced. Otherwise, this hotel is good in terms of location and price. Recommended for families.

As the name suggests, it is really a peaceful place to stay alone or with Family.

I stayed alone for 1 month 20 days on monthly basis & I can assure that you won’t get place to stay like this at the price they are offering.
Hotel Manager & Staff are very responsive and courteous.

They have covered 2 wheeler and 4 wheeler parking (max 1 car) at very nominal rate.

Rooms are decent enough in size and washrooms are also very clean.

For 20 days I stayed in Single bed room then another 1 month in double bed room as single occupant.

They have free Wifi and paid water bottles with terrace to dry your cloths. No food or room service available.  Washerman is available at call (3rd party paid service).
Lift is available on all floors.
Wheelchair entrance & stairs available.

Mostly occupants are working professional so its safe for girls too. They have all around CCTV cameras even on terrace.

Very close to Bells Road Post Office Bus Stop and Chepauk Stadium MRTS Railway. You can walk to the Marina Beach or take a bus.

Being in market area you will get ample option of restaurants and shopping places.
